Task Name: Identify and Remove Suspicious Browser Extensions
Objective: To detect and remove potentially harmful browser extensions to enhance browser security.

Steps Taken:

Opened the browserâ€™s extensions/add-ons manager.

Reviewed all installed extensions for necessity and legitimacy.

Checked permissions, ratings, and reviews for each extension.

Identified unused or suspicious extensions.

Removed flagged extensions.

Restarted the browser to verify performance.

Researched risks associated with malicious extensions.

List of Suspicious Extensions Found and Removed:

Example: DarkReader

Findings:

Unnecessary or suspicious extensions often request excessive permissions (e.g., access to all browsing data).

Poorly rated or unverified extensions pose security risks.

Best Practices Learned:

Install extensions only from trusted sources (e.g., official Chrome Web Store, Mozilla Add-ons).

Regularly audit and remove unused extensions.

Be cautious with extensions requesting unnecessary permissions.
